Tokyo scored top marks for helpfulness of locals, taxi service, local public transportation, and cleanliness of streets, ranking among the top ten in 13 of 16 categories in the survey.

The Cities Survey, which ranks each of the major tourist destinations in the world according to how well they scored across a number of different categories, is based on more than 54,000 reviews.

London scored highly for attractions (4th in the world), but less well on value for money (34th out of 37).

